  "why": "The paper explicitly focuses coverage-guided testing and generation directed at jailbreak attacks (i.e., inducing harmful/forbidden outputs), and its applications (real-time jailbreak detection, test-case prioritization, and coverage-guided jailbreak case generation) steer exploration toward that broad class of safety-violating behavior. However, the work does not target attacker-chosen specific outputs or narrowly specified attacker goals (e.g., a single chosen malicious label or a specific functional malware payload). The methods classify or generate 'jailbreak' vs 'normal' behavior and select prompts that increase coverage for jailbreaks, which corresponds to steering toward a predefined failure class rather than to a specific attacker-selected output.",
